        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 1:19PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 118 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lakesite, or 9 miles northeast of Chattanooga, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Cleveland, Soddy-Daisy, Walden, Lakesite, Ridgeside,
Harrison, Fairmount, South Cleveland, and Red Bank.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
